OL,3,CLee Anderson apologises after swearing
OL,4,Cat parliamentary security guard
OL,6,FWhen the guard repeated that the pass
OL,7,Fhad to be examined, Mr Anderson
OL,8,Fapproached them before saying "f***
OL,9,Fyou, I have a train to catch" and
OL,10,Fwalking out of the search post.
OL,12,FA complaint about the incident on
OL,13,FNovember 3 was upheld by Parliament's
OL,14,Fstandards commissioner.
OL,16,FMr Anderson, who is the MP for
OL,17,FAshfield, initially appealed against
OL,18,Fthe finding to the Independent Expert
OL,19,FPanel, but his case was dismissed on
OL,20,Fthe basis that it "failed to raise any
OL,21,Fsubstantive grounds."
