OL,6,FIn its findings, the watchdog
OL,7,Fhighlighted the "power imbalance"
OL,8,Fbetween the prominent MP and the
OL,9,Fsecurity officer and noted the
OL,10,Fimportance laid out in Parliament's
OL,11,Fbehaviour code not to "abuse" his
OL,12,Finfluence or authority.
OL,14,FThe panel had accepted Mr Anderson's
OL,15,Fevidence that he had faced challenging
OL,16,Fpersonal circumstances on the day in
OL,17,Fquestion and his "unacceptable
OL,18,Fbehaviour" was "not planned or
OL,19,Fpremeditated".
